ch.codebulb.lambdaomega.abstractions

Interface SequentialIFunctions<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    FunctionsI, SequentialI<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    OrderedSequential<T>, OrderedSequentialS<T>, SequentialIFunctionsS<T>, SequentialIS<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    L, M, S, V2.LV2

    public interface SequentialIFunctions<T>
extends SequentialI<T>, FunctionsI
    Adds a contract to work with functional interfaces to a SequentialI. None of these functions alter the original wrapped collection.

      • reduce

        default T reduce(T identity,
                 BinaryOperator<T> accumulator)
        Performs a "reduce" function with a single result f: (T, A) → R on the elements using an accumulator, injecting an identity element as the first accumulator value. This is the second step of the "map-reduce" algorithm. Other functions such as min(Function...) and sum(ToDoubleFunction) could actually be re-implemented using this function.

      • sortBy

        default List<T> sortBy(Function<T,V2<Function<? super T,Comparable>,Boolean>>... keyExtractors)
        Returns a List where the elements are sorted using the keyExtractors provided in order as a comparator on every element. Every keyExtractor is a function f: (T) → V2<f1, Boolean> where the return type is a V2; its 1st element is the actual keyExtractor function f1, its 2nd element is a Boolean specifying the sort order for that specific keyExtractor: true for ascending.
        See Also:
        #sortAscBy(Function...)}, {@link #sortBy(Function...)}
